nazole given systemically for more than 14 consecutive days should generally be avoided during treatment with bedaquiline unless the benefit is anticipated to outweigh the risk.', 'Major', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/169286/', '', 'Dirithromycin, Lincomycin, Clindamycin', 'Capreomycin, Pyrazinamide, Rifamycin, Streptomycin, Trimethoprim, Cycloserine, Isoniazid, Ethambutol, Pyridoxine, Ethionamide, Pretomanid, Aminosalicylic acid', 1767369485);
